00:01:18.788 --> 00:01:20.831
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:20.956 --> 00:01:22.708
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:22.958 --> 00:01:26.462
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:26.712 --> 00:01:28.839
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:28.964 --> 00:01:30.925
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:31.050 --> 00:01:33.177
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:33.344 --> 00:01:34.970
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:35.221 --> 00:01:38.599
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:39.308 --> 00:01:42.228
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:43.062 --> 00:01:43.604
<i>I...</i>

00:01:44.063 --> 00:01:44.730
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:44.855 --> 00:01:46.941
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:47.108 --> 00:01:47.983
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:48.109 --> 00:01:48.943
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:49.110 --> 00:01:50.736
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:50.986 --> 00:01:51.946
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:52.113 --> 00:01:52.863
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:52.988 --> 00:01:54.865
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:55.116 --> 00:01:55.991
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:56.200 --> 00:01:56.951
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:57.201 --> 00:01:58.619
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:58.953 --> 00:01:59.954
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:00.121 --> 00:02:01.080
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:01.205 --> 00:02:01.872
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:01.997 --> 00:02:03.499
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:08.629 --> 00:02:12.633
The Battle

00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:36.949
Griffith!

00:02:37.074 --> 00:02:38.159
Sir Griffith!

00:02:43.289 --> 00:02:45.833
Princess Charlotte,
what has happened?

00:02:50.921 --> 00:02:53.090
Please, take this...

00:02:56.969 --> 00:02:59.680
This is a necklace
made from lord stone.

00:03:00.472 --> 00:03:03.726
It is not so valuable, but it
belonged to the former queen...

00:03:04.101 --> 00:03:06.187
It was my mother's keepsake.

00:03:06.562 --> 00:03:08.189
Such a precious article of yours...

00:03:08.814 --> 00:03:09.982
I cannot accept it.

00:03:10.441 --> 00:03:12.693
Please, carry this with you.

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:19.575
The lord stone is made of two kinds of
stone, called the male and female stone...

00:03:19.992 --> 00:03:22.745
And, either type of the
stone will attract the other.

00:03:23.078 --> 00:03:27.708
It is said that persons who possess
companion stones shall not fail to be reunited.

00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:32.630
If you would bear this
necklace formed from the male stone...

00:03:33.881 --> 00:03:36.884
...it may be attracted to my
necklace, formed from the female stone.

00:03:37.718 --> 00:03:40.846
And thus, you ought to
return safely from the battlefield.

00:03:42.848 --> 00:03:45.142
Please, I would like you to take this.

00:03:46.644 --> 00:03:47.269
No...

00:03:49.021 --> 00:03:51.607
This is a precious
keepsake of yours, Princess.

00:03:51.774 --> 00:03:53.901
I cannot keep this as my possession.

00:03:54.276 --> 00:03:55.277
But...

00:03:57.905 --> 00:04:03.786
Therefore, I will return this safely
to you as soon as I return from battle.

00:04:07.915 --> 00:04:13.545
Honestly, never before has
the war filled me with such fear.

00:04:14.797 --> 00:04:17.216
Sir Griffith, please...

00:04:17.967 --> 00:04:19.510
Please, stay safe.

00:04:27.893 --> 00:04:29.395
Knight, please come forward.

00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:31.480
Y-Yes Ma'am...

00:04:31.855 --> 00:04:34.400
Please guard Sir
Griffith well during this battle.

00:04:36.402 --> 00:04:38.779
Certainly Ma'am, at the cost of my life.

00:04:43.617 --> 00:04:44.535
Let's go.

00:04:45.536 --> 00:04:46.412
All right...

00:05:01.302 --> 00:05:02.261
Charlotte.

00:05:04.513 --> 00:05:05.556
M-Mother.

00:05:06.140 --> 00:05:08.392
What do you think
you are doing, Charlotte?

00:05:08.934 --> 00:05:10.311
What do you mean?

00:05:11.145 --> 00:05:12.688
Do not feign ignorance.

00:05:12.938 --> 00:05:14.940
You gave that man of
lesser stature a present.

00:05:15.399 --> 00:05:19.069
It is not your concern who
I choose to give my property to!

00:05:19.278 --> 00:05:20.321
That is improper!

00:05:21.405 --> 00:05:23.782
You are a member of the royal house.

00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:28.329
Despite that fact, you gave a
present to that man of humble origins.

00:05:28.912 --> 00:05:31.582
When you talk to that man, concern
yourself with what others might think.

00:05:31.707 --> 00:05:34.084
You shall be mindful of your class.

00:05:35.085 --> 00:05:36.337
But, Mother...

00:05:36.712 --> 00:05:40.215
You have turned sixteen,
you are no longer a child.

00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:46.096
Charlotte!

00:06:04.448 --> 00:06:06.200
Look how popular we are!

00:06:06.367 --> 00:06:10.621
We are taking on the vanguard
position, it's a big responsibility.

00:06:10.954 --> 00:06:12.831
Hey, are you nervous?

00:06:13.082 --> 00:06:13.749
Nope!

00:06:14.124 --> 00:06:15.876
You seem to have lost your nerve.

00:06:16.877 --> 00:06:18.003
You're shaking.

00:06:18.212 --> 00:06:18.962
Shut up!

00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:20.881
I am just excited about the whole thing!

00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:24.510
Why is Griffith so late anyway...

00:06:58.252 --> 00:06:59.378
March!

00:07:34.455 --> 00:07:36.415
For me, a true friend is...

00:07:37.082 --> 00:07:40.043
...one who stands
equal on those terms.

00:08:30.511 --> 00:08:32.095
Oh no, why now?

00:08:32.763 --> 00:08:33.805
What's wrong?

00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:35.641
You look pale.

00:08:36.183 --> 00:08:37.142
It's nothing.

00:08:37.518 --> 00:08:39.520
Now, it's beginning!

00:08:50.447 --> 00:08:51.949
Charge!

00:08:52.950 --> 00:08:54.701
Charge!

00:09:35.742 --> 00:09:37.494
Damn, the battle's too confusing...

00:10:27.544 --> 00:10:28.795
It's you...

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:32.132
...the Hawks' only
female company commander.

00:10:32.507 --> 00:10:33.675
So what?

00:10:34.551 --> 00:10:35.802
I do not like it...

00:10:36.053 --> 00:10:38.513
...a mere woman such
as you, acting like a knight.

00:10:39.681 --> 00:10:43.894
How can women be of use in a fight, while
being so inferior to men in terms of power?

00:10:44.144 --> 00:10:45.646
If you think so, then come try me.

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:49.691
What's so funny?

00:10:50.025 --> 00:10:54.446
I assume that you comfort your
fellow soldiers during the night...

00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:55.572
What did you say?

00:10:55.822 --> 00:11:00.827
So, as a result of getting into Griffith's
bed, you must have won your rank...

00:11:01.078 --> 00:11:02.913
...as a company commander!

00:11:03.455 --> 00:11:07.584
I would like to experience the
charm that you've used on such men.

00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:10.837
You bastard!

00:11:16.176 --> 00:11:17.844
You bastard!

00:11:40.242 --> 00:11:42.494
A battlefield is a sanctuary for men.

00:11:42.744 --> 00:11:45.872
What outrageous conduct would lead a
woman like you to step into our sanctuary?

00:11:46.498 --> 00:11:49.710
I, the leader of the Blue Whale
Super Strong Heavy Assault Knights...

00:11:49.876 --> 00:11:52.838
...Lord Adon, will
teach you a lesson for this!

00:11:56.133 --> 00:11:56.633
He's coming!

00:12:13.150 --> 00:12:14.109
Big sister!

00:12:14.401 --> 00:12:15.861
Damn you!

00:12:16.903 --> 00:12:17.779
Idiot!

00:12:17.904 --> 00:12:18.613
Stay back!

00:12:25.287 --> 00:12:26.913
W-What a fighter...

00:12:27.038 --> 00:12:27.789
Caska!

00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:29.624
Get back, Judeau!

00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:30.917
I'll find a way to kill him!

00:12:31.293 --> 00:12:35.672
You all are cowards,
under her thumb no doubt.

00:12:35.922 --> 00:12:37.132
What was that?

00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:53.315
What will you do now?

00:12:53.440 --> 00:12:54.816
There is no ground behind you.

00:12:58.570 --> 00:13:00.530
Hey now, look at this.

00:13:01.156 --> 00:13:05.952
Well, I see, you rather look
pretty even though you are dressed...

00:13:06.578 --> 00:13:08.330
...in the manner of a man.

00:13:09.080 --> 00:13:11.541
Now, I will give you a chance.

00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:18.340
If you will be an obedient
captive, I will not kill you here.

00:13:18.548 --> 00:13:23.094
Being a captive means that you may
serve as a prostitute for my army, of course.

00:13:24.346 --> 00:13:25.555
Son of a bitch...

00:13:25.847 --> 00:13:28.975
So, you call me a son of a bitch...

00:13:29.476 --> 00:13:32.854
Then, you will be
buried by a bastard you hate!

00:13:33.313 --> 00:13:34.064
Big sister!

00:13:36.858 --> 00:13:38.109
What?

00:13:44.950 --> 00:13:46.201
This is not like you.

00:13:46.827 --> 00:13:47.869
Guts...

00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:49.871
Commander!

00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:50.872
Guts!

00:14:07.389 --> 00:14:08.598
Come on.

00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:13.103
I just want to swing my
sword against someone...

00:14:13.645 --> 00:14:16.147
...until I stop thinking
about everything else.

00:14:16.857 --> 00:14:19.150
Enough with your stupid remarks!

00:14:31.037 --> 00:14:33.540
Well done, I praise
you for blocking my strike!

00:14:34.416 --> 00:14:36.793
However, a fluke never happens twice!

00:14:42.674 --> 00:14:45.552
Can you defend against my special
strike that can even crush marble to pieces?

00:14:45.677 --> 00:14:46.887
This is the spearmanship...

00:14:47.012 --> 00:14:50.557
...that has been passed down through
the Coborlwitz family for 140 years.

00:14:52.392 --> 00:14:54.269
The ultimate secret technique...

00:14:55.437 --> 00:14:57.439
<i>Ganzansenpu...</i>

00:15:13.955 --> 00:15:15.582
<i>Ganzansenpu?</i>

00:15:16.082 --> 00:15:17.459
What the hell?

00:15:20.712 --> 00:15:22.172
A-Amazing...

00:15:22.589 --> 00:15:24.674
He beat that monster
with only two blows.

00:15:26.968 --> 00:15:28.303
Nothing less from our captain.

00:15:28.428 --> 00:15:29.471
Way to go!

00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:37.312
What's wrong?

00:15:37.604 --> 00:15:41.483
It's totally unlike you,
losing your edge in combat.

00:15:41.858 --> 00:15:43.568
Get it together, or you'll get killed.

00:15:48.740 --> 00:15:49.574
H-Hey!

00:16:04.005 --> 00:16:05.090
Guts!

00:16:14.766 --> 00:16:16.393
Guts!

00:16:16.643 --> 00:16:18.019
Caska!

00:17:09.154 --> 00:17:10.613
Never again...

00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:12.532
I'll never go in the water with my armor.

00:17:19.122 --> 00:17:20.165
Shit.

00:18:29.109 --> 00:18:31.861
She's got a serious fever, it looks bad.

00:18:58.847 --> 00:19:02.642
If I make a fire, the
enemy might spot it and find us.

00:19:10.400 --> 00:19:11.734
Dammit!

00:19:11.901 --> 00:19:13.486
I guess there's no other way.

00:19:17.657 --> 00:19:21.911
We did this sort of
thing once, it's no big deal!

00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:27.417
What the hell, with that fever of
hers she still thinks she can fight?

00:19:48.271 --> 00:19:49.939
So that's it.

00:19:56.029 --> 00:19:59.032
It's pretty tough to be a woman...

00:20:05.538 --> 00:20:06.956
Guts and Caska...

00:20:07.457 --> 00:20:11.461
The cliff was quite high, but a river was
running underneath it, so they must have...

00:20:12.545 --> 00:20:16.549
You know how Guts is,
they're probably alive, but...

00:20:16.716 --> 00:20:19.093
I couldn't see if they
landed safely from that fall.

00:20:19.427 --> 00:20:21.596
And the Captain was
already injured in the battle...

00:20:22.222 --> 00:20:24.224
Caska was not quite herself as well.

00:20:24.349 --> 00:20:27.602
We should get a search
party out there right away.

00:20:29.062 --> 00:20:31.606
Lord Griffith, you
must understand this...

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:36.361
...in a battle, our utmost
concern is to conquer the enemy.

00:20:36.444 --> 00:20:40.740
It is outrageous to use the soldiers
who have been gifted to you by the King...

00:20:40.865 --> 00:20:43.868
...to perform a search in the midst of
battle just to ensure the safety of a mere...

00:20:43.993 --> 00:20:45.203
...troop commander.

00:20:45.828 --> 00:20:50.708
Besides, it is a result of them
recklessly entering into single combat.

00:20:51.209 --> 00:20:53.002
No, that's not true...

00:20:57.257 --> 00:21:01.386
The leader of the Hawk's Raiders and
the famous female company commander.

00:21:01.594 --> 00:21:04.514
The two most skilled
commanders are together, aren't they?

00:21:04.889 --> 00:21:08.977
Supposedly, they are able
to take such troubles in stride.

00:21:09.477 --> 00:21:14.148
Indeed, I suppose they
will, if they are still alive.

00:22:02.655 --> 00:22:04.782
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:04.949 --> 00:22:08.453
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.662 --> 00:22:12.457
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.582 --> 00:22:15.460
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.170 --> 00:22:18.713
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:18.838 --> 00:22:19.964
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.089 --> 00:22:23.176
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.427 --> 00:22:27.305
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.430 --> 00:22:30.600
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:30.975 --> 00:22:34.228
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.729 --> 00:22:37.607
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.358 --> 00:22:41.361
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.236 --> 00:22:44.989
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:08.971 --> 00:23:13.976
Those who dedicate their lives to
another inevitably shed their own blood.

00:23:14.268 --> 00:23:19.899
Those who sacrifice themselves for
hopeless love cannot help shedding tears.

00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:23.528
Dream and hope, death and despair.

00:23:24.404 --> 00:23:31.744
Can one find a reason for living in the
act of believing and accepting all of this?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Together

